{
  "doc_id": "13520",
  "text": "Clinical presentation also varies depending on the subtype of AIP. In a recent international survey of 731 patients with AIP, the most common presenting symptom was obstructive jaundice [CITATION_1] . This occurred in approximately 75% of patients with Type 1 AIP and 50% of patients with type 2 AIP [CITATION_2] . However, patients with Type 2 AIP presented more commonly with acute pancreatitis (34%) and abdominal pain (68%) than patients with Type 1 AIP [CITATION_3] . Likewise, while inflammatory bowel disease is associated with AIP, it is more commonly found in patients with Type 2 disease [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] .",
